'''Near-Duros''' were [[Species/Legends|species]] that had evolved in slightly different directions to base-line [[Duros/Legends|Duros]] due to living in isolation from other Duros for many thousands of [[Standard year/Legends|years]]. This was often as a result of adapting to different environments. The most well-known of the Near-Duros species were the [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidians]].<ref name="GMR">{{GamerCite|2|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Duros}}</ref>

{{Species-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Yellow_Duro.jpg|thumb|150px|A possible yellow near-Duros.]]
A yellow-skinned Duros, which may have been a near-Duros, appeared in [[Star Wars (1977) 79|''Star Wars'' (1977) 79]].<ref name="Big Con">[[Star Wars (1977) 79|''Star Wars'' (1977) 79]]</ref><ref name="Tasty">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=1335#16585930|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2007-05-12|time=4:53 PM|quote=It's certainly possible, but then again there could be other explanations like mutation or albino.}}</ref>

